    1503 ACMS1 Computes Q-set stiffness, mass, and applied loads using Automated Component Modal Synthesis Main Index Remarks: 1.Lower bound parameter LUPF1 is typically set to 1.0 to exclude zero-frequency eigenvalues. Upper bound parameter LUPF2 is set to user’s F-max multiplied by UPFACT. The UPFACT keyword may be set via the DOMAINSOLVER Executive System command. 2.NSMP is set to the product of “i” and “j”, where “dmp=i” and “smp=j” are set on the MSC Nastran job submittal line. 3.The value of IREORTH may be set in the Bulk Data section with PARAM,IREORTH,value. 4.For an F-max value of 100.0 Hz, XFACT=1.0 will set the maximum threshold to 200.0 Hz. The values of XFACT and XFACTX may be set in the Bulk Data section with PARAM,XFACT and PARAM,XFACTX, respectively.IREORTH Input-integer-default=1000. Q-set size threshold to trigger periodic reorthogonalization of Q-set shapes. See Remark 3. EIGFILT Input-real-default=1.0E-13. Threshold for zero-frequency eigenvalue. XFACT Input-real-default= 1.0. Additional factor to determine upper bound for Q-set reorthogonalization. See Remark 4. XFACTX Input-real-default=2.0. Multiplier applied to user’s maximum frequency to determine maximum frequency for reorthogonalization. See Remark 4. ZROMASS Input-real-default=1.0E-12. Minimum threshold for zero eigenvalues. ZROVEC Input-real-default=1.0E-6. Threshold for zero frequency eigenvalues. RESFILT Input-real-default=1.0E-5. Filter for minimum threshold. ZROSTIFF Input-real-default=1.0E-8. Currently not used. TSIZE Input-integer-default=0: Size of global T-set RITZ2 Input-integer-default=0: Number of RITZ iterations to use during augmentation of Q-set vectors MMINFO Output-integer-default=0: Status flag. The default value indicates success. If nonzero, massless mechanisms may be present in the model. REDTYP Input-integer-default=3: Reduction Option. REDTYP=3 is for dynamic reduction.
    REDTYP=1 is for static reduction.
